Huawei, a telecommunication firm, clinched the best technology provider in the offshore oil and gas award at the 5th Nigerian International Energy Summit (NIES) 2022 in Abuja at the weekend. Commenting on the award during a media chat, a partner of Huawei and Executive Director, Emecom Technology & Consulting Ltd, Mr Ayodele Afenifero, said the firm’s technology solutions were the best not just for his organisation but also for other organisations in the oil and gas sector. He noted these were reasons for Huawei receiving the award for best technology provider in the offshore oil and gas category at the summit. He said: “Huawei has been a wonderful opportunity for my organisation based on the nature of their technology, product and solution portfolio that it has which speak directly to my customer needs. “People have been looking at the pipeline monitoring solution, the pipeline intrusion solution, and also the E and P storage infrastructure; talking about the storage Edorado, and many other storage applications.” Also speaking, the MD/CEO Monac Global Investment Ltd, Chinyere Okonkwo, said she has been a partner with Huawei for over 10 years. “I can tell you Huawei remains the best in having to get such strong durable technology, solutions and devices to meet the needs of your customers, especially in the oil and gas sectors like NNPC, PPMC, and others,” he said.